Interface OrderedCollectionOfIntKeyed<E extends Nullable & IntKeyed>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the element type

    public interface OrderedCollectionOfIntKeyed<E extends Nullable & IntKeyed>
extends OrderedCollection<E>
    Interface representing a specialisation of OrderedCollection for elements which have integer keys.

      • add

        E add(int key)
        Add an element with the specified key.

        On success this method appends the new element causing the OrderedCollection.shallowSize() to grow by one.

        Parameters:
        key - The key.
        Returns:
        The element.
        Throws:
        FieldException - If the operation is attempted on a semantically null collection.

      • insertAt

        E insertAt(int index,
           int key)
        Insert an element with the specified key at the specified index.

        On success the element is inserted at the specified index. Any elements at or above the specified index are moved up to make space. The OrderedCollection.shallowSize() grows by one.

        Parameters:
        index - The index. The valid range is [0, OrderedCollection.shallowSize()].
        key - The key.
        Returns:
        The element.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the index is out of range.
        FieldException - If the operation is attempted on a semantically null collection.

      • remove

        boolean remove(int key)
        Remove the first element with the specified key (if any).

        If an element is removed then all elements above the removed element (if any) are moved down to fill in the gap left by the removed element. The OrderedCollection.shallowSize() shrinks by one.

        Parameters:
        key - The key.
        Returns:
        True if an element was removed, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        FieldException - If the operation is attempted on a semantically null collection.
